ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend the course to anyone with a signal processing background looking to get a flavor of how biological systems can drive the models and algorithms in the field of computer vision.I'd also recommend it to anyone with a more biology/neuro background who is interested in getting a taste of signals and systems / image processing.
No. Lecture is too hard, while the homework assignments and tests are too easy.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: A new point of view even on familiar problems is always useful when working in an interdisciplinary field like Biomedical Engineering.
It is useful for me to know this field. But the biological side of this course is useless.
